title: Police: 2nd victim in Tampa, Florida, club shooting dies
content:
TAMPA, Fla. (AP) — A second victim has died as a result of a shooting at a Tampa strip club.
Tampa police announced in a news release Tuesday that 20-year-old Christopher Houston died late Monday from injuries suffered in the shooting at Club Rayne.
Marvin Douglass Lancaster III died at the scene, and six others were being treated at local hospitals Saturday, with injuries ranging from minor to very serious.
Crime Stoppers of Tampa Bay is offering a reward of up to $3,000 for information leading to the identification and arrest of a suspect.
